{{Infobox person | name = Pauliina Aalto | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 25 November 1967 | birth_place = [[Helsinki]] | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | other_names = | known_for = | education = | employer = | occupation = | title = | salary = | networth = | height = | weight = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | religion = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | signature = | website = | footnotes = | nationality = [[Finland|Finnish]] }} '''Pauliina Aalto''' (born 25 November 1967) was a [[Finland|Finnish]] [[Ten-pin bowling]] player at International level.
==Biography== Aalto was born in [[Helsinki]] in 1967. Aalto took up Ten-pin bowling in 1979. She took part World contest in 1993 where she won a Gold medal for the doubles. Between 1993 and 1997 she won numerous medals including 11 gold medals. Aalto and her partner organised a contest in 2008 in [[Lahti]] in Finland where they owned a bowls shop.<ref>[http://ebonite.com/news_events/news_detail/ebonite_international_to_serve_as_name_sponsor_for_lahti_open Ebonite International to serve as name sponsor for Lahti Open] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130121194250/http://ebonite.com/news_events/news_detail/ebonite_international_to_serve_as_name_sponsor_for_lahti_open |date=2013-01-21 }}, accessed August 2012</ref>
